Present location: BIBLIOTHECA ALEXANDRINA ANTIQUETIES MUSEUM [01/027] ALEXANDRIA BAAM
Name: Fragment of a Frieze
Description: A fragment of limestone frieze carved with embossed motifs of entwined vine leaves and bunches of grapes. The motifs are forming two circles, each containing four bunches of grapes and three vine leaves. Each group is connected to the next with three small bunches of grapes and three vine leaves from outside the circle.
